<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container container-narrow">
    <h2>Our Mission</h2>
    <p>When concepts evolve faster than institutions can standardize them, coordination failures compound. Legal definitions calcify while technical reality shifts. Translation breaks across domains. Nobody systematically maps this gap.</p>
    
    <p>We provide the first observatory tracking where technology terminology actually clusters versus where institutions say it should. Our quarterly reports serve journalists, policymakers, educators, and researchers during rapid technological change.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container container-narrow">
    <h2>What We Do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Track terminology evolution</strong> across research, legal, industry, and public domains</li>
      <li><strong>Document legal-technical misalignments</strong> with real-world impact analysis</li>
      <li><strong>Map conceptual clustering</strong> through co-occurrence analysis</li>
      <li><strong>Publish quarterly reports</strong> with transparent methodology and open data</li>
      <li><strong>Provide public API</strong> for programmatic access to terminology data</li>
      <li><strong>Serve rural communities</strong> through workshops expanding technology access</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

